  "response": "IVF (In Vitro Fertilization) significantly increases the chances of having twins or multiple babies compared to natural conception. Historically, the rates were quite high:\n\n1. In the past, when multiple embryos were routinely transferred, twin rates could be around 30-40%.\n\n2. Currently, with modern \"single embryo transfer\" practices, the twin rate is lower, around 10-15%.\n\n3. The multiple pregnancy rate depends on factors like:\n- Number of embryos transferred\n- Woman's age\n- Fertility clinic's protocols\n- Use of fertility medications\n\n4. Natural conception twin rate is approximately 1-2%, so IVF substantially increases this probability.\n\n5. Identical twins can still occur randomly, but fraternal twins are more likely with IVF due to multiple embryo transfer.\n\nModern fertility practices aim to reduce multiple pregnancy risks by recommending single embryo transfer when possible, which helps minimize potential complications for both mother and babies.",
